    <title>Escalation of Sensitive Discovery - Immediate Law Enforcement
      Notification Required</title>
  </head>
  <body>
    <p>Hello &lt;managers name, HR Manager&gt;, </p>
    <p>On the date of: <b>&lt;date&gt;</b> and time: <b>&lt;time&gt;</b>
      in time zone: <b>&lt;timezone&gt;</b> it was discovered that the
      user: <b>&lt;username&gt;</b> with account: <b>&lt;account
        name&gt;</b>, e-mail: <b>&lt;e-mail address&gt;</b>, system
      serial number: <b>&lt;serial number&gt;</b> and dept.: <b>&lt;department&gt;</b>
      was undergoing an investigation for an alert, or event that
      occurred on: <b>&lt;date/time of event&gt;</b>. For your records
      you can reference the following ticket number: <b>&lt;ticket
        number&gt; </b></p>
    <p>On the date noted, during our investigation it was determined
      that the above stated user may have CSAM stored in the folder: <b>&lt;folder
        name / direct path&gt;</b>. At the time of: &lt;date/time&gt;
      when the material was first noted, the session has been terminated
      and logged out. </p>
    <p>With respect to local and federal laws the material must be
      reported in a timely manner and must be preserved for PD and FBI.
      &lt;username&gt; has not been notified. The user was told that the
      event is being escalated to touch, use or modify the system in
      chat (screen shot provided) and is currently awaiting further
      assistance. </p>
    <p>From this point forward all investigatory work will cease and
      must be handed over to law enforcement. SOC Team will not be
      furthering the investigation due to legalities, and safety reasons
      / concerns. </p>
